Getting Started:

To get started with this project, you'll need to have the Dart SDK installed on your machine. Follow the steps below to set everything up:

Check Dart SDK version:
Ensure you have the correct Dart SDK installed by running the following command in your terminal:



dart --version
Clone the repository:
Clone this repository to your local machine using the following Git command:



git clone https://github.com/your_username/dart_fundamentals_project.git
Navigate to the project directory:
After cloning the repository, navigate to the root directory:


cd dart_fundamentals_project
Run the project:
You can run the main Dart file to see the output of the sample code:


dart run lib/src/main.dart
Project Structure:

This project follows a simple structure, with the main code residing in the lib/src folder:

plaintext
Copy code
```/lib
  /src
    main.dart  # Entry point of the project```
Sample Code:

Hereâ€™s an example of basic Dart code included in this project:

dart

```void main() {
  String greeting = 'Hello, Dart!';
  for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
    print('$i: $greeting');
  }
}```
This program prints the greeting "Hello, Dart!" three times with an index, showcasing how loops and string interpolation work in Dart.

